pr_title: doc: Fix a typo (add a missing period)
pr_body: A section on [*Explaining BSD*](https://docs.freebsd.org/en/articles/explaining-bsd/#_how_is_bsd_developed_and_updated) (`... before committing them In extreme cases, a core team member ...`) is missing a period. This commit just adds that period.

Managing Clones

https://docs.freebsd.org/en/books/handbook/zfs/

'Creating a clone makes it an exact copy of the state the dataset as it was when taking the snapshot.'

â€“ is fixed to 'the state the dataset was in'.

Bugzilla

https://docs.freebsd.org/en/articles/committers-guide/#bugzilla

'Be sure that if you commit a fix or suggestion found in the PR database to close it.'

-- is fixed to 'Be sure that, if you commit a fix or suggestion found in the PR database, close it.'

This is a 2023Q2 status report for the ***Integrate mfsBSD into the release building tools*** project.

I used the status report template, and made sure to follow the guidelines -- e.g. one sentence per line. Thanks everyone for handling all the status reports, and please let me know if there's anything you'd like me to add to this PR :+1: :+1:

This means they tend to get out of sync with the tools in base.
This project aims to address that problem.
```
